London Fashion Week is here and we better prepare to see mind blowing designs by artists and designers from all over the world. The 5-day event sees fashion and activities that celebrate the latest trends from more than 100 international designers. Ranging from spanning womenswear, menswear and gender-neutral designs. The clothing showcase happens twice a year, in February and September, in London. The limited-edition tickets have to be booked online or you have to receive a personal invite from the Designer's press team. This month, the event will run from 18th to 22nd; invited guests will experience the catwalk shows, talks and have a unique shopping experience. The designers and their teams will host pop-up shops from previous and current designs.